Hi guys,

It seems that it is not possible to add the TOC macro to a template when it is between a section or div macro.

For example, if we create a template with the following code:
{noformat}
{section}
{column:witdh=70%}
Text
{column}
{column:witdh=30%}
{div:class=noprint}
{toc:indent=22px|printable=false}
{div}
{column}
{section}
{noformat}
When we create a page with it, it renders the TOC macro as rich text.

If we have the following code:
{noformat}
{toc:indent=22px|printable=false}
{section}
{column:witdh=70%}
Text
{column}
{column:witdh=30%}
{div:class=noprint}
{div}
{column}
{section}
{noformat}
When we create a page with this template, the TOC macro is rendered properly.

However, when we use another macro such as Warning macro within the section:
{noformat}
{section}
{column:witdh=70%}
Text
{column}
{column:witdh=30%}
{div:class=noprint}
{warning}
{div}
{column}
{section}
{noformat}
When we create a page with this template, the warning macro functions properly.

Is this expected behavior for the TOC macro?

Cheers,
Ricardo

