h3.Problem Description
Creating table from wiki markup or upgraded content from wiki markup, wrap the cells with p tag and create some unnecessary margin. It has been fixed in 4.1.7 and it didn't replicatable in Confluence 4.2.x. However it does occur in Confluence 4.3 and 4.3.1. See image below for more information.

*Table created from Rich text editor*
!tablebug-rte.png!

*Table created from Wiki markup*
!tablebug-wiki.png!

h3.Steps to replicate
# Click _Insert >> Wiki Markup_.
# Create table from there, for example like the following.
{noformat}
||Col_1||Col_2||Col_3||
|Row|Row|Row|
|Row|Row|Row|
{noformat}
# Now create table using Rich text editor and notice the difference

h3.Workaround
Insert the following on custom stylesheet. Either from _Confluence Admin >> Stylesheet_ or _Space Admin >> Stylesheet_.
{noformat}
.confluenceTh p, .confluenceTd p {
	margin:0 !important;
}
{noformat}

